Across four consecutive episodes, Alex and the fitness user demonstrate distinct progressions in routine, mood, and training intensity. In session sess_003 (2025-01-20, 45 mins), Alex reported mood 7/10 and 7 hours sleep, noting a change from the usual 20-minute zombie state to waking ready. Alex fixed Jira ticket #4102 (button state update) during a product launch freeze and attended social events with Sam. By sess_004 (2025-01-27, 40 mins), Alex’s mood dropped to 6/10 with 6 hours sleep following a stakeholder meeting where Sam suggested reviewing numbers. Work delays involved Jira ticket #4150. Alex planned a 4-mile hike with Sam, Jess, and Mike, and a March wedding attendance.

Concurrently, the fitness user in session DC-003 (2023-10-16, 48 mins) completed Week 3 of a half-marathon plan. The user ran 14 miles, hitting a wall at mile 11, and adjusted fueling to take gels at mile 6 or 7 next time. The user modified lifting schedules, switching Sunday deadlifts to leg extensions to prevent fatigue, and logged 170g protein daily. In session DC-004 (2023-10-23, 50 mins), the user finished Week 4, running 16 miles in 2:20 without a wall. The user increased deadlifts to 235lbs for 8 reps and adopted dynamic carb intake (300g on run days, 200g on rest days). New habits included waking naturally at 6 AM, 10-minute meditation, and adding salt tabs. Both users show increased social engagement and specific technical or physical adjustments to their respective goals, with Alex managing work stress through humor and the fitness user optimizing nutrition and recovery protocols.", "metadata": {"type": "group_summary", "episode_ids": ["therapy_chat_12_ep_003", "therapy_chat_12_dx_fitness_coaching_003", "therapy_chat_12_ep_004", "therapy_chat_12_dx_fitness_coaching_004"]}}

